name: adexchangeseller

fields.name: status
fields.desc:
Status of this ad unit. Possible values are:
NEW: Indicates that the ad unit was created within the last seven days and does not yet have any activity associated with it.

ACTIVE: Indicates that there has been activity on this ad unit in the last seven days.

INACTIVE: Indicates that there has been no activity on this ad unit in the last seven days.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: The external description of the channel.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: The locations in which ads appear. (Only valid for content and mobile content ads). Acceptable values for content ads are: TOP_LEFT, TOP_CENTER, TOP_RIGHT, MIDDLE_LEFT, MIDDLE_CENTER, MIDDLE_RIGHT, BOTTOM_LEFT, BOTTOM_CENTER, BOTTOM_RIGHT, MULTIPLE_LOCATIONS. Acceptable values for mobile content ads are: TOP, MIDDLE, BOTTOM, MULTIPLE_LOCATIONS.

fields.name: siteLanguage

fields.name: totalMatchedRows
fields.desc: The total number of rows matched by the report request. Fewer rows may be returned in the response due to being limited by the row count requested or the report row limit.

fields.name: totals
fields.desc: The totals of the report. This is the same length as any other row in the report; cells corresponding to dimension columns are empty.

fields.name: warnings
fields.desc: Any warnings associated with generation of the report.

fields.name: averages
fields.desc: The averages of the report. This is the same length as any other row in the report; cells corresponding to dimension columns are empty.

fields.name: headers
fields.desc: The header information of the columns requested in the report. This is a list of headers; one for each dimension in the request, followed by one for each metric in the request.

fields.name: currency
fields.desc: The currency of this column. Only present if the header type is METRIC_CURRENCY.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the header.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the header; one of DIMENSION, METRIC_TALLY, METRIC_RATIO, or METRIC_CURRENCY.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind this is, in this case adexchangeseller#report.

fields.name: rows
fields.desc: The output rows of the report. Each row is a list of cells; one for each dimension in the request, followed by one for each metric in the request. The dimension cells contain strings, and the metric cells contain numbers.

methods.name: generate
methods.desc: Generate an Ad Exchange report based on the report request sent in the query parameters. Returns the result as JSON; to retrieve output in CSV format specify "alt=csv" as a query parameter.

requiredQueryParams.name: startDate
requiredQueryParams.desc: Start of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.

requiredQueryParams.name: endDate
requiredQueryParams.desc: End of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.

optinalQueryParams.name: dimension
optinalQueryParams.desc: Dimensions to base the report on.

optinalQueryParams.name: filter
optinalQueryParams.desc: Filters to be run on the report.

optinalQueryParams.name: metric
optinalQueryParams.desc: Numeric columns to include in the report.

optinalQueryParams.name: startIndex
optinalQueryParams.desc: Index of the first row of report data to return.

optinalQueryParams.name: locale
optinalQueryParams.desc: Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local language. Defaults to "en_US" if not specified.

optinalQueryParams.name: maxResults
optinalQueryParams.desc: The maximum number of rows of report data to return.

optinalQueryParams.name: sort
optinalQueryParams.desc: The name of a dimension or metric to sort the resulting report on, optionally prefixed with "+" to sort ascending or "-" to sort descending. If no prefix is specified, the column is sorted ascending.
